00076   bool GPS_BroadcastEphemerisAndAlmanacArray::AllocateArray()
00077   {
00078     unsigned i = 0;
00079     if( m_array != NULL )
00080     {
00081       if( m_arrayLength == GPS_NUMBER_VALID_PRNS )
00082         return true; // already allocated
00083       else
00084         return false; // error
00085     }
00086     m_array = new GPS_structOrbitParameters[GPS_NUMBER_VALID_PRNS];
00087     if( m_array == NULL )
00088       return false;
00089     m_arrayLength = GPS_NUMBER_VALID_PRNS;
00090 
00091     // Initialize all to zero.
00092     for( i = 0; i < GPS_NUMBER_VALID_PRNS; i++ )
00093     {
00094       memset( &m_array[i], 0, sizeof(GPS_structOrbitParameters) );
00095     }
00096 
00097     return true;
00098   }

00101   bool GPS_BroadcastEphemerisAndAlmanacArray::AddEphemeris( const unsigned short prn, const GPS_structEphemeris &eph )
00102   {
00103     unsigned short index = 0;
00104 
00105     if( m_arrayLength == 0 )
00106     {
00107       if( !AllocateArray() )
00108         return false;
00109     }
00110 
00111     if( !GetIndexGivenPRN( prn, index ) )
00112       return false;
00113 
00114     // The previous ephemeris is set based on what was the current prior this update.
00115     m_array[index].previousEph = m_array[index].currentEph;
00116     m_array[index].currentEph  = eph;
00117 
00118     return true;
00119   }

00139   bool GPS_BroadcastEphemerisAndAlmanacArray::GetEphemeris( 
00140     const unsigned short prn, //!< The desired GPS PRN. (1-32 GPS, 120-138 SBAS).
00141     GPS_structEphemeris &eph, //!< A reference to an ephemeris struct in which to store the data.
00142     bool &isAvailable,        //!< This boolean indicates if ephemeris data is available or not.
00143     char iode                 //!< The issue of data for the ephemeris, -1 means get the most current.
00144     )
00145   {
00146     unsigned short index = 0;
00147 
00148     if( m_arrayLength == 0 )
00149     {
00150       isAvailable = false;
00151       return true;
00152     }
00153     
00154     if( !GetIndexGivenPRN( prn, index ) )
00155       return false;
00156 
00157     // check the prn to see if any ephemeris information is available.
00158     if( m_array[index].currentEph.prn == 0 )
00159     {
00160       isAvailable = false;
00161       return true;
00162     }
00163 
00164     isAvailable = true;
00165     if( iode == -1 )
00166     {
00167       eph = m_array[index].currentEph;      
00168     }
00169     else
00170     {
00171       if( m_array[index].currentEph.iode == iode )
00172       {
00173         eph = m_array[index].currentEph;
00174       }
00175       else if( m_array[index].previousEph.iode == iode )
00176       {
00177         eph = m_array[index].previousEph;
00178       }
00179       else
00180       {
00181         isAvailable = false;
00182       }
00183     }
00184     return true;
00185   }

00187   bool GPS_BroadcastEphemerisAndAlmanacArray::IsEphemerisAvailable( 
00188     const unsigned short prn, //!< The desired GPS PRN. (1-32 GPS, 120-138 SBAS).
00189     bool &isAvailable,        //!< This boolean indicates if ephemeris data is available or not.
00190     char iode                 //!< The issue of data for the ephemeris, -1 means get the most current.
00191     )

00193     unsigned short index = 0;
00194 
00195     // Check if there is any data in the array.
00196     if( m_arrayLength == 0 )
00197     { 
00198       isAvailable = false;
00199       return true;
00200     }
00201     
00202     if( !GetIndexGivenPRN( prn, index ) )
00203       return false;
00204 
00205     // check the prn to see if any ephemeris information is available.
00206     if( m_array[index].currentEph.prn == 0 )
00207     {
00208       isAvailable = false;
00209       return true;
00210     }
00211 
00212     if( iode == -1 )
00213     {
00214       isAvailable = true;
00215     }
00216     else
00217     {
00218       if( m_array[index].currentEph.iode == iode )
00219       {
00220         isAvailable = true;
00221       }
00222       else if( m_array[index].previousEph.iode == iode )
00223       {
00224         isAvailable = true;
00225       }
00226       else
00227       {
00228         isAvailable = false;
00229       }
00230     }
00231     return true;
00232   }

00236   bool GPS_BroadcastEphemerisAndAlmanacArray::GetIndexGivenPRN( const unsigned short prn, unsigned short &index )
00237   {
00238     // GPS 1-32
00239     // Pseudolites are 33-37
00240     // SBAS is 120-138
00241     // WAAS, EGNOS, MSAS
00242     //
00243     // WAAS:
00244     // AOR-W       122
00245     // Anik        138
00246     // POR         134
00247     // PanAm       135
00248     //
00249     // EGNOS:
00250     // AOR-E       120
00251     // Artemis     124
00252     // IOR-W       126
00253     // IOR-E       131
00254     //
00255     // MSAS:
00256     // MTSAT-1     129
00257     // MTSAT-2     137
00258     //
00259     // The index mapping is as follows:
00260     // PRN 1-37    maps to indidex 0-36
00261     // PRN 38-40   maps to indices 37-39 (reserved mappings)
00262     // PRN 120-138 maps to indicex 40-58
00263     
00264 
00265     // check unsupported prn values
00266     if( prn == 0 )
00267     {
00268       return false;
00269     }
00270     if( prn > 38 && prn < 120 )
00271     {
00272       return false;
00273     }
00274     if( prn > 138 )
00275     {
00276       return false;
00277     }
00278     
00279     if( prn < 38 )
00280     {
00281       index = prn - 1;
00282     }
00283     if( prn > 119 && prn < 139 )
00284     {
00285       index = prn - 80;
00286     }
00287     return true;
00288   }

00325   {

00327 
00328     m_nrValidObs = 0;
00329 
00330     for( i = 0; i < GNSS_RXDATA_NR_CHANNELS; i++ )
00331     {
00332       memset( &(m_ObsArray[i]), 0, sizeof(GNSS_structMeasurement) );
00333       memset( &(m_prev_ObsArray[i]), 0, sizeof(GNSS_structMeasurement) );

00348   {

00353       return false;

00356     {
00357       return false;

00359 
00360 #ifndef _CRT_SECURE_NO_DEPRECATE
00361     if( fopen_s( &m_fid, path, "rb" ) != 0 )
00362       return false;

00365 #endif
00366     if( m_fid == NULL )    
00367       return false;
00368     
00369     isValidPath = true;
00370 
00371     m_rxDataType = rxType;
00372 
00373     return true;

00376   bool GNSS_RxData::LoadNext( bool &endOfStream )
00377   {
00378     BOOL result = FALSE;
00379     BOOL wasEndOfFileReached = FALSE;
00380     BOOL wasMessageFound = FALSE;
00381     unsigned filePosition = 0;
00382     unsigned short messageID = 0;
00383     NOVATELOEM4_enumMessageType messageType;
00384     unsigned numberBadCRC = 0;
00385 
00386     //  A NovAtel OEM4 header information struct.
00387     NOVATELOEM4_structBinaryHeader header; 
00388 
00389     // An array of struct_NOVATELOEM4_RANGE.
00390     NOVATELOEM4_structObservation obsArray[GNSS_RXDATA_NR_CHANNELS];
00391 
00392     // A gps ephemeris struct.
00393     GPS_structEphemeris eph;
00394     unsigned prn;            // The PRN.
00395     unsigned reference_week; // The ephemeris reference week.
00396     unsigned reference_tow;  // The ephemeris reference time of week.
00397     unsigned tow;            // The tow associated with the start of Subframe1.
00398 
00399     unsigned nrValidObs;
00400     unsigned i = 0;
00401     unsigned j = 0;
00402     bool isAvailable;  // A boolean used in checking if ephemeris is available.
00403 
00404 
00405     endOfStream = false;
00406 
00407     if( m_fid == NULL )
00408       return false;
00409 
00410     // Copy the current observations into the previous storage.
00411     m_prev_nrValidObs = m_nrValidObs;
00412     for( i = 0; i < m_nrValidObs; i++ )
00413     {
00414       m_prev_ObsArray[i] = m_ObsArray[i];
00415       memset( &(m_ObsArray[i]), 0, sizeof(GNSS_structMeasurement) ); // Initialize to zero.
00416     }
00417 
00418     switch( m_rxDataType )
00419     {
00420     case GNSS_RXDATA_NOVATELOEM4:
00421       {  
00422         while( !wasEndOfFileReached && !wasMessageFound )
00423         {
00424           result = NOVATELOEM4_FindNextMessageInFile( 
00425             m_fid,
00426             m_message,
00427             GNSS_RXDATA_MSG_LENGTH,
00428             &wasEndOfFileReached,
00429             &wasMessageFound,
00430             &filePosition,
00431             &m_messageLength,
00432             &messageID,
00433             &numberBadCRC 
00434             );
00435           if( result == FALSE )
00436             return false;
00437           
00438           messageType = (NOVATELOEM4_enumMessageType)messageID;
00439           if( wasMessageFound && messageType != NOVATELOEM4_RANGEB )
00440           { 
00441             if( messageType == NOVATELOEM4_RAWEPHEMB )
00442             {
00443               memset( &eph, 0, sizeof(GPS_structEphemeris) );
00444              
00445               result = NOVATELOEM4_DecodeRAWEPHEMB(
00446                 m_message,
00447                 m_messageLength,
00448                 &header,
00449                 &prn,
00450                 &reference_week,
00451                 &reference_tow,
00452                 &tow,
00453                 &eph.iodc,
00454                 &eph.iode,
00455                 &eph.toe,
00456                 &eph.toc,
00457                 &eph.week,
00458                 &eph.health,
00459                 &eph.alert_flag,
00460                 &eph.anti_spoof,
00461                 &eph.code_on_L2,
00462                 &eph.ura,
00463                 &eph.L2_P_data_flag,
00464                 &eph.fit_interval_flag,
00465                 &eph.age_of_data_offset,
00466                 &eph.tgd,
00467                 &eph.af2,
00468                 &eph.af1,
00469                 &eph.af0,
00470                 &eph.m0,
00471                 &eph.delta_n,
00472                 &eph.ecc,
00473                 &eph.sqrta,
00474                 &eph.omega0,
00475                 &eph.i0,
00476                 &eph.w,
00477                 &eph.omegadot,
00478                 &eph.idot,
00479                 &eph.cuc,
00480                 &eph.cus,
00481                 &eph.crc,
00482                 &eph.crs,
00483                 &eph.cic,
00484                 &eph.cis );
00485               if( result )
00486               {
00487                 eph.prn = prn;
00488                 
00489                 result = m_EphAlmArray.AddEphemeris( eph.prn, eph );
00490                 if( !result )
00491                 {
00492                   // An error occurred.
00493                   return false;
00494                 }
00495               }
00496             }
00497             wasMessageFound = false;
00498           }
00499         }
00500         if( wasMessageFound && messageType == NOVATELOEM4_RANGEB )
00501         {
00502           m_nrValidObs = 0;
00503           m_nrGPSL1Obs = 0;
00504           
00505           result = NOVATELOEM4_DecodeRANGEB( 
00506             m_message,
00507             m_messageLength,
00508             &header,
00509             obsArray,
00510             GNSS_RXDATA_NR_CHANNELS,
00511             &nrValidObs 
00512             );
00513           if( result == FALSE )
00514             return false;
00515 
00516           // Set the receiver time of the observation set.
00517           m_pvt.time.gps_week = header.gpsWeek;
00518           m_pvt.time.gps_tow  = header.gpsMilliSeconds / 1000.0;
00519 
00520           for( i = 0; i < nrValidObs && i < GNSS_RXDATA_NR_CHANNELS; i++ )
00521           {
00522             m_ObsArray[i].channel   = obsArray[i].trackingStatus.channelNumber;
00523             m_ObsArray[i].id        = obsArray[i].prn;
00524 
00525             m_ObsArray[i].system    = (GNSS_enumSystem)obsArray[i].trackingStatus.eSatelliteSystem;
00526             m_ObsArray[i].codeType  = (GNSS_enumCodeType)obsArray[i].trackingStatus.eCodeType;
00527             m_ObsArray[i].freqType  = (GNSS_enumFrequency)obsArray[i].trackingStatus.eFrequency;
00528 
00529             if( m_ObsArray[i].system == GNSS_GPS &&
00530               m_ObsArray[i].freqType == GNSS_GPSL1 )
00531             {
00532               m_nrGPSL1Obs++;
00533             }
00534 
00535             m_ObsArray[i].psr       = obsArray[i].psr;
00536             m_ObsArray[i].adr       = -1.0*obsArray[i].adr;
00537             m_ObsArray[i].doppler   = obsArray[i].doppler;
00538             m_ObsArray[i].cno       = obsArray[i].cno;
00539             m_ObsArray[i].locktime  = obsArray[i].locktime;
00540     
00541             if( obsArray[i].psrstd < 0.2 )
00542               m_ObsArray[i].stdev_psr     = 0.2f;
00543             else
00544               m_ObsArray[i].stdev_psr     = obsArray[i].psrstd; 
00545 
00546             m_ObsArray[i].stdev_psr     = 1.4f;
00547             
00548             if( obsArray[i].adrstd < 0.0025 )
00549               m_ObsArray[i].stdev_adr     = 0.0025f; // these are in cycles!.              
00550             else
00551               m_ObsArray[i].stdev_adr     = obsArray[i].adrstd; // these are in cycles!.
00552 
00553             if( obsArray[i].adrstd < 0.0001 )
00554               int gaa = 99;
00555 
00556             m_ObsArray[i].stdev_adr     = 0.05f; // these are in cycles!.
00557             
00558             m_ObsArray[i].stdev_doppler = 0.5f; // Hz
00559 
00560             m_ObsArray[i].psr_smoothed      = 0.0;
00561             m_ObsArray[i].psr_predicted     = 0.0;
00562             m_ObsArray[i].doppler_predicted = 0.0;
00563             m_ObsArray[i].azimuthRads       = 0.0;
00564             m_ObsArray[i].elevationRads     = 0.0;
00565 
00566             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isActive = 1;
00567             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isCodeLocked   = obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isCodeLocked;
00568             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isPhaseLocked  = obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isPhaseLocked;
00569             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isParityValid  = obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isParityKnown;
00570             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isPsrValid     = obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isCodeLocked;
00571             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrValid     = obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isPhaseLocked & obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isParityKnown;
00572             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDopplerValid = obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isCodeLocked;            
00573             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isGrouped      = obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isGrouped;
00574             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAutoAssigned = !obsArray[i].trackingStatus.isForcedAssignment;
00575             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isCarrierSmoothed     = 0; // not yet known
00576 
00577             // Check if ephemeris information is available
00578             if( !m_EphAlmArray.IsEphemerisAvailable( m_ObsArray[i].id, isAvailable ) )
00579               return false;
00580 
00581             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isEphemerisValid      = isAvailable;
00582 
00583             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAlmanacValid        = 0; // not yet known
00584             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveElevationMask  = 0; // not yet known
00585             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveCNoMask        = 0; // not yet known
00586             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveLockTimeMask   = 0; // not yet known
00587             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotUserRejected     = 1; // assume not rejected
00588             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotPsrRejected      = 1; // assume not rejected
00589             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotAdrRejected      = 1; // assume not rejected
00590             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotDopplerRejected  = 1; // assume not rejected
00591             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNoCycleSlipDetected = 1; // assume no slip
00592             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isUsedInPosSolution   = 0; // not yet known
00593             m_ObsArray[i].flags.isUsedInVelSolution   = 0; // not yet known
00594 
00595             if( m_DisableTropoCorrection )
00596               m_ObsArray[i].flags.useTropoCorrection          = 0;
00597             else
00598               m_ObsArray[i].flags.useTropoCorrection          = 1; // defaults to yes
00599 
00600             if( m_DisableIonoCorrection )
00601               m_ObsArray[i].flags.useBroadcastIonoCorrection  = 0;
00602             else
00603               m_ObsArray[i].flags.useBroadcastIonoCorrection  = 1; // default to yes
00604             
00605             m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcTropoDry = 0;
00606             m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcTropoWet = 0;
00607             m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcIono = 0;
00608             m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcSatClk = 0;
00609             m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcReserved1 = 0;
00610             m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcReserved2 = 0;
00611             m_ObsArray[i].corrections.rrcSatClkDrift = 0;
00612             m_ObsArray[i].corrections.rrcReserved1 = 0;

00622 
00623             m_nrValidObs++;
00624           }
00625           
00626         }
00627         if( wasEndOfFileReached )

00640     // Search for matching observations in the previous set of data to pass on static information
00641     // like ambiguities.
00642     for( i = 0; i < m_nrValidObs; i++ )
00643     {
00644       for( j = 0; j < m_prev_nrValidObs; j++ )
00645       {
00646         if( m_ObsArray[i].codeType == m_prev_ObsArray[j].codeType &&
00647           m_ObsArray[i].freqType == m_prev_ObsArray[j].freqType &&
00648           m_ObsArray[i].system == m_prev_ObsArray[j].system &&
00649           m_ObsArray[i].id == m_prev_ObsArray[j].id ) // Note should also check that channels are the same if real time!
00650         {
00651           m_ObsArray[i].ambiguity = m_prev_ObsArray[j].ambiguity;
00652           break;
00653         }
00654       }
00655     }
00656 
00657 
00658     return true;
00659   }

00661   bool GNSS_RxData::SetInitialPVT( 
00662     const double latitudeRads,   //!< The latitude [rad].
00663     const double longitudeRads,  //!< The longitude [rad].
00664     const double height,         //!< The orthometric height [m].
00665     const double vn,             //!< The northing velocity [m/s].
00666     const double ve,             //!< The easting velocity [m/s].
00667     const double vup,            //!< The up velocity [m/s].
00668     const double clk,            //!< The clock offset [m].
00669     const double clkdrift,       //!< The clock drift [m/s].
00670     const double std_lat,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the latitude [m].
00671     const double std_lon,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the longitude [m].
00672     const double std_hgt,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the height [m].
00673     const double std_vn,         //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the northing velocity [m/s].
00674     const double std_ve,         //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the easting velocity [m/s].
00675     const double std_vup,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the up velocity [m/s].
00676     const double std_clk,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the clock offset [m].
00677     const double std_clkdrift,   //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the clock drift [m/s].
00678     const double undulation      //!< The undulation if known [m].
00679     )
00680   {
00681     bool result;
00682 
00683     result = UpdatePositionAndRxClock(
00684       latitudeRads,
00685       longitudeRads,
00686       height,
00687       clk,
00688       std_lat,
00689       std_lon,
00690       std_hgt,
00691       std_clk );
00692     if( !result )
00693       return false;
00694 
00695     result = UpdateVelocityAndClockDrift(
00696       vn,
00697       ve,
00698       vup,
00699       clkdrift,
00700       std_vn,
00701       std_ve,
00702       std_vup,
00703       std_clkdrift );
00704     if( !result )
00705       return false;
00706 
00707     //m_pvt.dop;     //!< All the associated DOP information for this solution.
00708 
00709     if( std_lat == 0.0 && std_lon == 0.0 && std_hgt == 0.0 )
00710     {
00711       m_pvt.std_lat = 1e-03;
00712       m_pvt.std_lon = 1e-03;
00713       m_pvt.std_hgt = 1e-03;      
00714       m_pvt.isPositionConstrained = 1;
00715     }
00716 
00717     m_pvt.isHeightConstrained = 0;
00718     m_pvt.isClockConstrained = 0;
00719     m_pvt.isSolutionBasedOnEphemeris = 0;
00720 
00721     m_pvt.undulation = undulation;
00722 
00723     // Set the previous pvt as well.
00724     m_prev_pvt = m_pvt;
00725     
00726     return true;
00727   }

00729 
00730   bool GNSS_RxData::UpdatePositionAndRxClock( 
00731     const double latitudeRads,   //!< The latitude [rad].
00732     const double longitudeRads,  //!< The longitude [rad].
00733     const double height,         //!< The orthometric height [m].
00734     const double clk,            //!< The clock offset [m].
00735     const double std_lat,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the latitude [m].
00736     const double std_lon,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the longitude [m].
00737     const double std_hgt,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the height [m].
00738     const double std_clk         //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the clock offset [m].
00739     )
00740   {
00741     bool result;
00742     m_pvt.latitude   = latitudeRads;
00743     m_pvt.longitude  = longitudeRads;
00744     m_pvt.height     = height;
00745     
00746     m_pvt.latitudeDegs  = latitudeRads*RAD2DEG;
00747     m_pvt.longitudeDegs = longitudeRads*RAD2DEG;
00748 
00749     result = GetDMS( 
00750       m_pvt.latitudeDegs, 
00751       m_pvt.lat_dms.degrees, 
00752       m_pvt.lat_dms.minutes, 
00753       m_pvt.lat_dms.seconds, 
00754       (char*)m_pvt.lat_dms.dms_str, 24 );
00755     if( result == false )
00756       return false;
00757 
00758     result = GetDMS( 
00759       m_pvt.longitudeDegs, 
00760       m_pvt.lon_dms.degrees, 
00761       m_pvt.lon_dms.minutes, 
00762       m_pvt.lon_dms.seconds, 
00763       (char*)m_pvt.lon_dms.dms_str, 24 );
00764     if( result == false )
00765       return false;
00766 
00767     if( GEODESY_ConvertGeodeticCurvilinearToEarthFixedCartesianCoordinates(
00768       GEODESY_REFERENCE_ELLIPSE_WGS84,
00769       m_pvt.latitude,
00770       m_pvt.longitude,
00771       m_pvt.height,
00772       &m_pvt.x,
00773       &m_pvt.y,
00774       &m_pvt.z ) == FALSE )
00775     {
00776       return false;
00777     }
00778     m_pvt.clockOffset = clk;
00779 
00780     m_pvt.std_lat = std_lat;
00781     m_pvt.std_lon = std_lon;
00782     m_pvt.std_hgt = std_hgt;
00783     m_pvt.std_clk = std_clk;
00784     
00785     return true;
00786   }
00787 
00788   bool GNSS_RxData::UpdateVelocityAndClockDrift( 
00789     const double vn,             //!< The northing velocity [m/s].
00790     const double ve,             //!< The easting velocity [m/s].
00791     const double vup,            //!< The up velocity [m/s].
00792     const double clkdrift,       //!< The clock drift [m/s].
00793     const double std_vn,         //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the northing velocity [m/s].
00794     const double std_ve,         //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the easting velocity [m/s].
00795     const double std_vup,        //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the up velocity [m/s].
00796     const double std_clkdrift    //!< The standard deviation uncertainty in the clock drift [m/s].
00797     )
00798   {
00799     m_pvt.vn  = vn;
00800     m_pvt.ve  = ve;
00801     m_pvt.vup = vup;
00802 
00803     GEODESY_RotateVectorFromLocalGeodeticFrameToEarthFixedFrame(
00804       m_pvt.latitude,
00805       m_pvt.longitude,
00806       m_pvt.vn,
00807       m_pvt.ve,
00808       m_pvt.vup,
00809       &m_pvt.vx,
00810       &m_pvt.vy,
00811       &m_pvt.vz );
00812     
00813     m_pvt.clockDrift = clkdrift;
00814 
00815     m_pvt.std_vn  = std_vn;
00816     m_pvt.std_ve  = std_ve;
00817     m_pvt.std_vup = std_vup;
00818     m_pvt.std_clkdrift  = std_clkdrift;
00819 
00820     return true;
00821   }

00825   //static 
00826   bool GNSS_RxData::GetDMS( 
00827     const double angleDegs,  //!< The angle [degrees].
00828     short &degrees,          //!< The degrees part.
00829     short &minutes,          //!< The minutes part.
00830     float &seconds,          //!< The seconds part.
00831     char *dms_str,           //!< A DMS string e.g. dms_str = "-180'59'59.9999\""
00832     const unsigned maxLength_dms_str //!< The maximum length of the dms_str string.
00833     )
00834   {
00835     bool isNegative = false;
00836     double angle = angleDegs;
00837     int result = 0;
00838 
00839     if( angleDegs < 0 )
00840     {
00841       isNegative = true;
00842       angle = -angleDegs;
00843     }
00844     else
00845     {
00846       angle = angleDegs;
00847     }
00848 
00849     degrees = static_cast<short>(floor(angle));
00850     minutes = static_cast<short>(floor((angle - degrees)*60.0));
00851     seconds = static_cast<float>((angle - degrees - minutes/60.0)*3600.0);
00852 
00853     if( isNegative )
00854       degrees = -degrees;
00855 
00856 #ifndef _CRT_SECURE_NO_DEPRECATE
00857     result = sprintf_s( 
00858       dms_str, 
00859       maxLength_dms_str, 
00860       "%+4d%c%02d\'%02.4f\"", 
00861       degrees, 
00862       176, // the degrees symbol
00863       minutes,
00864       seconds );
00865 #else
00866     result = sprintf( 
00867       dms_str,     
00868       "%+4d%c%02d\'%02.4f\"", 
00869       degrees, 
00870       176, // the degrees symbol
00871       minutes,
00872       seconds );
00873 #endif
00874 
00875     if( result == -1 )
00876       return false;
00877 
00878     return true;
00879   }

00881 
00882   bool GNSS_RxData::CheckForCycleSlips_UsingPhaseRatePrediction( 
00883     const double nrThresholdCycles //!< The maximum number of cycles to use as the threshold to detect a slip [cycles].
00884     )
00885   {
00886     unsigned i = 0;
00887     unsigned j = 0;
00888     double t_prev = 0.0;
00889     double t = 0.0;
00890     double dt = 0.0;
00891     double phase_diff = 0.0; // The difference between the predicted phase and the measured phase.
00892     double predicted_phase = 0.0;
00893     double mean_doppler = 0.0;
00894 
00895     static double max_dif = 0.0;
00896 
00897     t_prev = m_prev_pvt.time.gps_week*SECONDS_IN_WEEK + m_prev_pvt.time.gps_tow;
00898     t = m_pvt.time.gps_week*SECONDS_IN_WEEK + m_pvt.time.gps_tow;
00899     dt = t - t_prev;
00900     if( dt <= 0.0 )
00901     {
00902       return false;
00903     }
00904     if( dt > 60.0 ) // The phase rate prediction method is not going to work well.
00905     {
00906       return true;
00907     }
00908             
00909     for( i = 0; i < m_nrValidObs; i++ )
00910     {
00911       for( j = 0; j < m_prev_nrValidObs; j++ )
00912       {
00913         if( m_ObsArray[i].system == m_prev_ObsArray[j].system &&
00914           m_ObsArray[i].id == m_prev_ObsArray[j].id &&
00915           m_ObsArray[i].freqType == m_prev_ObsArray[j].freqType )
00916         {
00917           // channel matching is not perforned.
00918           // This should be done if this a real time receiver data.
00919           // However, since the data source is generally not known for
00920           // post processing software, it is not performed here.
00921           if( m_ObsArray[i].flags.isPhaseLocked && m_prev_ObsArray[j].flags.isPhaseLocked )
00922           {
00923             mean_doppler = (m_ObsArray[i].doppler + m_prev_ObsArray[j].doppler)/2.0;
00924 
00925             predicted_phase = m_prev_ObsArray[j].adr - mean_doppler * dt; // GDM_BEWARE Doppler sign convention
00926 
00927             phase_diff = predicted_phase - m_ObsArray[i].adr;
00928 
00929             if( fabs(phase_diff) > max_dif )
00930               max_dif = fabs(phase_diff);
00931             if( fabs(phase_diff) > nrThresholdCycles )
00932             {
00933               m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNoCycleSlipDetected = 0; // Indicate a cycle slip has occured.
00934             }
00935             else
00936             {
00937               m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNoCycleSlipDetected = 1; // No cycle slip detected.
00938             }
00939             break;
00940           }
00941         }
00942       }
00943     }
00944 
00945     return true;
00946   }

00949   bool GNSS_RxData::DebugPrintObservationArray( const char *filepath )
00950   {
00951     unsigned i = 0;
00952     unsigned j = 0;
00953     Matrix X(100,m_nrValidObs);
00954     
00955     if( filepath == NULL )
00956       return false;
00957 
00958 
00959     for( i = 0; i < m_nrValidObs; i++ )
00960     {
00961       j = 0;
00962       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].channel; j++;
00963       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].id; j++;       //!< The unique id for this channel (eg PRN for GPS).    
00964       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].system; j++;   //!< The satellite system associated with this channel.
00965       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].codeType; j++; //!< The code type for this channel.
00966       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].freqType; j++; //!< The frequency type for this channel.
00967 
00968       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isActive; j++;              //!< This flag indicates that the channel is active for use. If this is not set, no other flags are valid for use.
00969       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isCodeLocked; j++;          //!< Indicates if the code tracking is locked.
00970       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isPhaseLocked; j++;         //!< Indicates if the phase tracking is locked.
00971       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isParityValid; j++;         //!< Indicates if the phase parity if valid.      
00972       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isPsrValid; j++;            //!< Indicates if the pseudorange valid for use.
00973       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrValid; j++;            //!< Indicates if the ADR is valid for use.
00974       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDopplerValid; j++;        //!< Indicates if the Doppler if valid for use.
00975       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isGrouped; j++;             //!< Indicates if this channel has another associated channel. eg. L1 and L2 measurements.
00976       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAutoAssigned; j++;        //!< Indicates if the channel was receiver assigned (otherwise, the user forced this channel assignment).
00977       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isCarrierSmoothed; j++;     //!< Indicates if the pseudorange has carrier smoothing enabled.
00978       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isEphemerisValid; j++;      //!< Indicates if this channel has valid associated ephemeris information. 
00979       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAlmanacValid; j++;        //!< Indicates if this channel has valid associated almanac information.
00980       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveElevationMask; j++;  //!< Indicates if the satellite tracked is above the elevation mask.    
00981       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveCNoMask; j++;        //!< Indciates if the channel's C/No is above a threshold value.
00982       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAboveLockTimeMask; j++;   //!< Indicates if the channel's locktime is above a treshold value.
00983       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotUserRejected; j++;     //!< Indicates if the user has not forced the rejection of this channel or PRN.
00984       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotPsrRejected; j++;      //!< Indicates if the pseudorange was not rejetced (ie Fault Detection and Exclusion).
00985       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotAdrRejected; j++;      //!< Indicates if the ADR was not rejetced (ie Fault Detection and Exclusion).
00986       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNotDopplerRejected; j++;  //!< Indicates if the Doppler was not rejected (ie Fault Detection and Exclusion).
00987       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isNoCycleSlipDetected; j++; //!< Indicates that no cycle slip has occurred at this epoch.
00988       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isUsedInPosSolution; j++;   //!< Indicates if some part (pseudorange) of this channel's measurement was used in the position solution.
00989       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isUsedInVelSolution; j++;   //!< Indicates if some part (Doppler) of this channel's measurement was used in the velocity solution.
00990       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isAdrUsedInSolution; j++;   //!< Indicates if the the ADR is used in the solution.
00991       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDifferentialPsrAvailable; j++;     //!< Indicates if a matching pseudrange observation is available from another receiver.
00992       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDifferentialDopplerAvailable; j++; //!< Indicates if a matching Doppler observation is available from another receiver.
00993       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isDifferentialAdrAvailable; j++;     //!< Indicates if a matching ADR observation is available from another receiver.
00994       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.useTropoCorrection; j++;         //!< Indicates that the tropospheric correction should be applied.
00995       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.useBroadcastIonoCorrection; j++; //!< Indicates that the broadcast ionospheric correction should be applied.
00996       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isTimeDifferntialPsrAvailable; j++;
00997       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].flags.isTimeDifferntialDopplerAvailable; j++;
00998 
00999       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].week; j++;  //!< The measurement gps week (at 'transmit' time) [weeks].
01000       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].tow; j++;   //!< The measurement gps time of week (at 'transmit' time) [s].
01001 
01002       // The actual measurements.
01003       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].psr; j++;               //!< The pseudorange measurement [m].
01004       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].adr; j++;               //!< The carrier phase or accumulated Doppler range measurement [cycles].
01005       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].doppler; j++;           //!< The Doppler measurement for this channel [Hz].
01006       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].cno; j++;               //!< The carrier to noise density ratio for this channel [dB-Hz]
01007       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].locktime; j++;          //!< The number of seconds of continous phase tracking (no known cycle slips) [s].
01008 
01009       // The variance information associated with the actual measurements.
01010       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].stdev_psr; j++;         //!< The estimated pseudorange measurement standard deviation [m].
01011       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].stdev_adr; j++;         //!< The estimated accumulated Doppler range measurement standard deviation [cycles].
01012       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].stdev_doppler; j++;     //!< The estimated Doppler measurement standard deviation [Hz].
01013 
01014       // Derived information.
01015       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].psr_misclosure; j++;    //!< The measured psr minus the computed psr estimate [m].
01016       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].doppler_misclosure; j++;//!< The measured Doppler minus the computed Doppler estimate [m].
01017       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].range; j++;             //!< The best estimate of the geometric range between the antenna and the satellite [m].
01018       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].rangerate; j++;         //!< The best estimate of the geometric range rate between the antenna and the satellite [m/s].
01019       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].psr_smoothed; j++;      //!< The carrier smoothed pseudorange if available [m].
01020       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].psr_predicted; j++;     //!< The predicted pseudorange based on the satellite position, user position, and current clock offset [m].
01021       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].ambiguity; j++;         //!< The estimated integer component of the adr. This may be the single or double differenced ambiguity [].
01022       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].doppler_predicted; j++; //!< The predicted Doppler based on user position, velocity, satellite position, velocity and clock rate [Hz].
01023       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].azimuthRads; j++;       //!< The associated satellite azimuth for this channel [rad].
01024       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].elevationRads; j++;     //!< The associated satellite elevation for this channel  [rad].
01025 
01026 
01027       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].index_differential; j++;      //!< The channel index of a matching differential observation. -1 means there is no matching channel.
01028       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].index_time_differential; j++; //!< The channel index of a matching time differential observation. -1 means there is no matching channel.
01029 
01030       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].index_differential_adr; j++;  //!< The channel index of a matching differential observation. -1 means there is no matching channel.
01031       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].index_ambiguity_state; j++;   //!< The index into the state vector for this ambiguity state. -1 not estimated.
01032       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].adr_misclosure; j++;          //!< The measured ADR minus the computed ADR estimate [m]. This is likely a differential quantity.
01033 
01034       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].H_p[0]; j++; //!< The design matrix row relating the pseudorange measurements to the position solution. dP/d(lat), dP/d(lon), dP/d(hgt).
01035       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].H_p[1]; j++;
01036       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].H_p[2]; j++;
01037       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].H_v[0]; j++; //!< The design matrix row relating the Doppler measurements to the velocity solution. dD/d(lat), dD/d(lon), dD/d(hgt).
01038       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].H_v[1]; j++;
01039       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].H_v[2]; j++;
01040 
01041       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.dX; j++; //!< The corrections associated with this channel.
01042       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.dY; j++;
01043       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.dZ; j++;
01044       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcIono; j++;
01045       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcReserved1; j++;
01046       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcReserved2; j++;
01047       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcSatClk; j++;
01048       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcTropoDry; j++;
01049       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.prcTropoWet; j++;
01050       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].corrections.rrcReserved1; j++;
01051 
01052       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].residuals.psrResidual; j++;   //!< The post-adjustment (filtering) measurement residual associated with this channel.
01053       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].residuals.dopplerResidual; j++;
01054       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].residuals.adrResidual; j++;
01055       X[j][i] = m_ObsArray[i].residuals.reserved; j++;      
01056     }
01057     X.Redim(j,m_nrValidObs);
01058 
01059     X.Print( filepath, 12 ); // print to the file in append mode.
01060 
01061     return true;
01062   }

01066   bool GNSS_RxData::Debug_WriteSuperMsg80CharsWide(
01067     char* buffer,                    //!< A large character buffer (8KB min).
01068     const unsigned maxBufferLength,  //!< The maximum buffer length [bytes].
01069     const double referenceLatitude,  //!< Reference position latitude [rad].
01070     const double referenceLongitude, //!< Reference position longitude [rad].
01071     const double referenceHeight,    //!< Reference position height [m].
01072     unsigned& nrBytesInBuffer )      //!< The number of bytes set in the buffer.
01073   {
01074     unsigned i = 0;
01075     unsigned j = 0;
01076     int week = -1;
01077     int tmpi = 0;
01078 
01079     unsigned scount = 0;
01080 
01081     double x = 0;
01082     double y = 0;
01083     double z = 0;
01084 
01085     double n_err  = 0.0;
01086     double e_err  = 0.0;
01087     double up_err = 0.0;
01088     double dtmp = 0.0;
01089     double v_azimuth = 0.0;
01090 
01091     if( maxBufferLength < 1024*8 )
01092     {
01093       nrBytesInBuffer = 0;
01094       return false;
01095     }
